00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:41.720 align:middle line:84%
So let's just start a little
bit at the beginning right now,

00:01:41.720 --> 00:01:44.180 align:middle line:84%
and that is as a
teenager, and what

00:01:44.180 --> 00:01:48.050 align:middle line:84%
started happening in history
class to you in this lifetime.

00:01:48.050 --> 00:01:50.450 align:middle line:10%
>>DE STEFANO: Well, it's
been all my life for sure

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:52.640 align:middle line:10%
that I had this connection
with other beings

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:55.310 align:middle line:10%
from other dimensions
that for me were just

00:01:55.310 --> 00:01:57.140 align:middle line:10%
part of the family.

00:01:57.140 --> 00:02:01.640 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea that they
were from other sides.

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:07.340 align:middle line:84%
And there was one day when I was
12 years old that they told me,

00:02:07.340 --> 00:02:08.824 align:middle line:90%
you won't see us anymore.

00:02:08.824 --> 00:02:12.860 align:middle line:84%
You won't be able to watch
us to see our shapes anymore,

00:02:12.860 --> 00:02:14.630 align:middle line:90%
but you will start to remember.

00:02:14.630 --> 00:02:18.920 align:middle line:84%
Next Sunday-- next Monday,
you will start to remember.

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:21.830 align:middle line:84%
So pay attention to
everything we taught to you,

00:02:21.830 --> 00:02:26.810 align:middle line:84%
and just write it down
and make drawings.

00:02:26.810 --> 00:02:30.710 align:middle line:90%
Don't let it in your mind.

00:02:30.710 --> 00:02:32.430 align:middle line:90%
That was the only advice.

00:02:32.430 --> 00:02:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And so I stopped
seeing them, and--

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:37.492 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: How was that for you?

00:02:37.492 --> 00:02:38.867 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: That
was very tough

00:02:38.867 --> 00:02:40.790 align:middle line:84%
because it was like
losing part of the family.

00:02:40.790 --> 00:02:42.890 align:middle line:84%
Like if they just
said, OK, we have

00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:44.940 align:middle line:90%
to move to another country and--

00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:45.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Left you.

00:02:45.740 --> 00:02:47.870 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Maybe we
can call sometime, but--

00:02:47.870 --> 00:02:48.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:02:48.750 --> 00:02:49.570 align:middle line:90%
You're an orphan.

00:02:49.570 --> 00:02:51.403 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah,
yeah, it felt like that.

00:02:51.403 --> 00:02:56.600 align:middle line:90%
It was like losing my gran--

00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:59.250 align:middle line:84%
like a big brother or
something like this,

00:02:59.250 --> 00:03:02.720 align:middle line:84%
like other family, someone
who was guiding me.

00:03:02.720 --> 00:03:04.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
so now here we go.

00:03:04.590 --> 00:03:05.660 align:middle line:90%
You're on your own.

00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:06.460 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:03:06.460 --> 00:03:09.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And let's hop to when
you start experiencing things

00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:12.320 align:middle line:84%
through common information that
was coming up in your life,

00:03:12.320 --> 00:03:13.940 align:middle line:84%
and boom, the
memories come back.

00:03:13.940 --> 00:03:18.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, so that
Monday or Tuesday I think.

00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:22.130 align:middle line:84%
We had this history
class, and the teacher

00:03:22.130 --> 00:03:27.660 align:middle line:84%
gave us these copies with
like ancient history.

00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:31.903 align:middle line:84%
So from the very beginning,
very beginning 3,500 years--

00:03:31.903 --> 00:03:33.320 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, when
humanity began.

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:37.273 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, well, the
first civilizations and stuff.

00:03:37.273 --> 00:03:38.940 align:middle line:84%
And there was a picture
of the pyramids,

00:03:38.940 --> 00:03:41.750 align:middle line:84%
which until that moment
for me was nothing.

00:03:41.750 --> 00:03:48.920 align:middle line:84%
But when I saw it, I had a
headache, like a pain here,

00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:53.960 align:middle line:84%
and I just saw like everything
move like in a tunnel.

00:03:53.960 --> 00:03:57.230 align:middle line:84%
And I saw the
pyramids, only one.

00:03:57.230 --> 00:04:00.170 align:middle line:84%
Actually it took many years
until I saw the three.

00:04:00.170 --> 00:04:02.957 align:middle line:84%
I was only seeing one,
the one and the middle.

00:04:02.957 --> 00:04:05.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Was that because you
were seeing from different time

00:04:05.540 --> 00:04:06.770 align:middle line:90%
frames?

00:04:06.770 --> 00:04:09.110 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: I thought it
was different time frame,

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:13.190 align:middle line:84%
but also I thought
that I was emotionally

00:04:13.190 --> 00:04:15.659 align:middle line:84%
linked to that pyramid
even more than the others.

00:04:15.659 --> 00:04:16.459 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:04:16.459 --> 00:04:19.960 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So my mind just
got rid of the other ones

00:04:19.960 --> 00:04:20.760 align:middle line:90%
and said--

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:23.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Focused on
what was important, yeah.

00:04:23.930 --> 00:04:28.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: But
I saw it white,

00:04:28.070 --> 00:04:29.820 align:middle line:84%
and everything was
very different.

00:04:29.820 --> 00:04:30.950 align:middle line:90%
There were trees.

00:04:30.950 --> 00:04:32.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, it was
covered at one time

00:04:32.870 --> 00:04:34.285 align:middle line:90%
in white-- it was white.

00:04:34.285 --> 00:04:35.660 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
it was limestone,

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:37.290 align:middle line:90%
but it was covered in white.

00:04:37.290 --> 00:04:38.090 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:04:38.090 --> 00:04:39.692 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And
white and alabaster.

00:04:39.692 --> 00:04:41.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Alabaster,
correct, yeah.

00:04:41.150 --> 00:04:43.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So
they were shining--

00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:43.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:04:43.430 --> 00:04:44.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Like
stars on Earth,

00:04:44.710 --> 00:04:45.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:48.920 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And I saw that
image, and the second image

00:04:48.920 --> 00:04:50.990 align:middle line:84%
I had was in front
of the Sphinx,

00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:53.180 align:middle line:90%
which was like a red lion.

00:04:53.180 --> 00:04:57.230 align:middle line:84%
And I was a woman
aside of my husband,

00:04:57.230 --> 00:04:59.330 align:middle line:90%
and I was really worried.

00:04:59.330 --> 00:05:02.540 align:middle line:84%
And that was the first
memories I got that day.

00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:06.170 align:middle line:84%
And from that moment on, every
day, I had another memory.

00:05:06.170 --> 00:05:08.510 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it was
part of the language.

00:05:08.510 --> 00:05:11.090 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes something that
happened in my family.

00:05:11.090 --> 00:05:15.000 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes something that
happened in the village.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:16.580 align:middle line:90%
So it was all mixed.

00:05:16.580 --> 00:05:20.120 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't really put the
whole picture together

00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:23.937 align:middle line:90%
until I was like 17, 18.

00:05:23.937 --> 00:05:25.520 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And what
did you figure out?

00:05:25.520 --> 00:05:27.230 align:middle line:90%
What was that story about?

00:05:27.230 --> 00:05:28.940 align:middle line:84%
Why was it important
you were seeing it?

00:05:28.940 --> 00:05:32.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: I realized that
I was remembering that story

00:05:32.150 --> 00:05:35.210 align:middle line:84%
because I was in the
mirror time of that story,

00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:40.610 align:middle line:84%
like I am right at the other
side of the timeline of that.

00:05:40.610 --> 00:05:42.740 align:middle line:90%
So I'm mirroring that moment.

00:05:42.740 --> 00:05:46.260 align:middle line:84%
That's why for me was more
important than all the rest.

00:05:46.260 --> 00:05:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And also because I
decided something

00:05:50.580 --> 00:05:56.140 align:middle line:84%
in that moment in that life
that I said in that time,

00:05:56.140 --> 00:06:00.050 align:middle line:84%
I had to finish it in my
mirrored time, which is now.

00:06:00.050 --> 00:06:01.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, so what did it--

00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:02.770 align:middle line:90%
A, we'll get into mirrored time.

00:06:02.770 --> 00:06:05.570 align:middle line:90%
What is it you had to finish?

00:06:05.570 --> 00:06:10.430 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: I had to do a
reconnection of the network

00:06:10.430 --> 00:06:12.740 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:06:12.740 --> 00:06:16.190 align:middle line:84%
For that time, it was different
because it was Leo time,

00:06:16.190 --> 00:06:21.660 align:middle line:84%
so it was all about the
governments and the families,

00:06:21.660 --> 00:06:25.340 align:middle line:84%
the structure of the main
families ruling the planet

00:06:25.340 --> 00:06:29.840 align:middle line:84%
and trying to settle the power
in the main sources, which

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:32.840 align:middle line:84%
were like the pyramids or other
pyramids around the world.

00:06:32.840 --> 00:06:35.150 align:middle line:84%
And for the new
time, it would be

00:06:35.150 --> 00:06:40.130 align:middle line:84%
networks, how every individual
should be its own government

00:06:40.130 --> 00:06:43.850 align:middle line:84%
and creating a new network
besides the pyramids,

00:06:43.850 --> 00:06:46.230 align:middle line:84%
like creating it
in a different way.

00:06:46.230 --> 00:06:48.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which is the
timeline we're in now.

00:06:48.140 --> 00:06:49.550 align:middle line:84%
That's what's
required of us now.

00:06:49.550 --> 00:06:54.305 align:middle line:84%
Did you get a sense of the
dynastic period at all?

00:06:54.305 --> 00:06:55.430 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Dynastic, no.

00:06:55.430 --> 00:06:58.625 align:middle line:84%
Well, it was a dynasty,
but it was not Egyptian.

00:06:58.625 --> 00:06:59.425 align:middle line:90%
OK,

00:06:59.425 --> 00:06:59.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, it wasn't--

00:06:59.690 --> 00:07:01.280 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: It was
Egypt, but it was not--

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:01.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It was not.

00:07:01.580 --> 00:07:02.360 align:middle line:90%
So it might have been even--

00:07:02.360 --> 00:07:03.652 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Egyptian culture.

00:07:03.652 --> 00:07:06.472 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so if some
of the people and some

00:07:06.472 --> 00:07:08.180 align:middle line:84%
of the traditions that
talk about the age

00:07:08.180 --> 00:07:12.710 align:middle line:84%
of the Great Pyramid put it at
85,000 to 200,000 years old,

00:07:12.710 --> 00:07:14.900 align:middle line:84%
you could have been
looking at history prior

00:07:14.900 --> 00:07:16.192 align:middle line:90%
to any of the dynastic periods.

00:07:16.192 --> 00:07:17.400 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yes, of course.

00:07:17.400 --> 00:07:18.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:20.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: The
people in Egypt

00:07:20.930 --> 00:07:23.360 align:middle line:84%
that were from the
dynastic period, they

00:07:23.360 --> 00:07:25.070 align:middle line:90%
rebuilt the pyramids.

00:07:25.070 --> 00:07:26.100 align:middle line:90%
They did some works.

00:07:26.100 --> 00:07:26.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:07:26.900 --> 00:07:28.260 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Repairing them.

00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:29.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They weren't
the originators.

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:30.650 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: But they
weren't the original ones

00:07:30.650 --> 00:07:31.550 align:middle line:90%
creating them.

00:07:31.550 --> 00:07:34.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now let's talk
about the opposite timeline

00:07:34.700 --> 00:07:36.140 align:middle line:90%
and what you mean by that.

00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:39.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are
some theories that

00:07:39.830 --> 00:07:42.770 align:middle line:84%
may very well be
true that everything

00:07:42.770 --> 00:07:44.550 align:middle line:90%
has its mirrored opposite.

00:07:44.550 --> 00:07:48.620 align:middle line:84%
So whatever we are in now has
us in our mirrored opposite

00:07:48.620 --> 00:07:50.060 align:middle line:90%
in that timeline.

00:07:50.060 --> 00:07:52.140 align:middle line:84%
Explain it how you
see it, understand it,

00:07:52.140 --> 00:07:54.890 align:middle line:84%
and why-- how did
you know that was it?

00:07:54.890 --> 00:07:56.570 align:middle line:84%
Because of what
you know and came

00:07:56.570 --> 00:08:00.110 align:middle line:84%
to do that you figured that
out, or is there something maybe

00:08:00.110 --> 00:08:03.170 align:middle line:90%
more linear as an explanation?

00:08:03.170 --> 00:08:07.320 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Well, I understood
that when I was 16 or 17,

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:11.810 align:middle line:84%
I guess, about how we
can interpret things,

00:08:11.810 --> 00:08:15.788 align:middle line:84%
like for example, from the
third dimension point of view

00:08:15.788 --> 00:08:17.330 align:middle line:84%
or the fourth
dimension point of view

00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:20.210 align:middle line:84%
is dependent on which dimension
you want to explain something.

00:08:20.210 --> 00:08:21.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:08:21.010 --> 00:08:23.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: It changes,
so it's not linear.

00:08:23.240 --> 00:08:25.160 align:middle line:84%
The explanation
is not like, this

00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:27.830 align:middle line:84%
happens because of
this and this and this.

00:08:27.830 --> 00:08:30.830 align:middle line:84%
It's according to which
dimension you explain it.

00:08:30.830 --> 00:08:34.590 align:middle line:84%
So from our point of
view, that is the past,

00:08:34.590 --> 00:08:36.830 align:middle line:84%
so it's something
that already happened.

00:08:36.830 --> 00:08:40.250 align:middle line:84%
And that condition,
our civilization today,

00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:41.172 align:middle line:90%
through time.

00:08:41.172 --> 00:08:43.130 align:middle line:84%
From the point of view
of the fourth dimension,

00:08:43.130 --> 00:08:44.810 align:middle line:90%
that is still happening.

00:08:44.810 --> 00:08:47.240 align:middle line:84%
And because that's
still happening,

00:08:47.240 --> 00:08:50.510 align:middle line:84%
it's conditioning us
today as our actions today

00:08:50.510 --> 00:08:53.750 align:middle line:84%
is conditioning what
is happening there,

00:08:53.750 --> 00:08:56.600 align:middle line:84%
so it depends on
the point of view.

00:08:56.600 --> 00:08:59.240 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is that
all in the universe

00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:02.330 align:middle line:84%
has a positive and a
negative, and everything

00:09:02.330 --> 00:09:05.540 align:middle line:84%
flows in a cycle, ups
and downs, in and out.

00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:10.400 align:middle line:84%
So everything moves in
this kind of cycles.

00:09:10.400 --> 00:09:15.140 align:middle line:84%
So when we talk about time,
a way of understanding this

00:09:15.140 --> 00:09:18.290 align:middle line:90%
is like talking about vibration.

