00:28:37.990 --> 00:28:42.200 align:middle line:84%
eventually it will be the
worst system if it keeps going.

00:28:42.200 --> 00:28:48.700 align:middle line:84%
So for example, feudalism was
a perfect system for Europe.

00:28:48.700 --> 00:28:52.750 align:middle line:84%
Kingdoms was a perfect
system for Middle East.

00:28:52.750 --> 00:28:56.150 align:middle line:84%
But in this period, we
say, those are bad things.

00:28:56.150 --> 00:28:56.950 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:28:56.950 --> 00:28:59.230 align:middle line:84%
It's because we are
going into another wave,

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:02.320 align:middle line:84%
into democracy or
something different that

00:29:02.320 --> 00:29:04.620 align:middle line:90%
is coming with networks.

00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:06.480 align:middle line:90%
And democracy is now old too.

00:29:06.480 --> 00:29:10.480 align:middle line:84%
It's not working anymore, so
we have to go to another thing.

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:13.980 align:middle line:84%
So this kind of
things, It doesn't

00:29:13.980 --> 00:29:17.730 align:middle line:84%
mean that democracy wasn't good,
that republics wasn't good,

00:29:17.730 --> 00:29:21.300 align:middle line:84%
that kingdoms weren't good,
that feudalism wasn't good,

00:29:21.300 --> 00:29:22.920 align:middle line:90%
that dictatorship wasn't good.

00:29:22.920 --> 00:29:24.783 align:middle line:90%
It was the perfect--

00:29:24.783 --> 00:29:26.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Solution
in this moment.

00:29:26.200 --> 00:29:26.790 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Solution
in that moment.

00:29:26.790 --> 00:29:27.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:27.590 --> 00:29:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And there was
no other option that moment

00:29:29.940 --> 00:29:31.625 align:middle line:90%
because of the context.

00:29:31.625 --> 00:29:33.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And also the
consciousness of the people.

00:29:33.750 --> 00:29:34.738 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:29:34.738 --> 00:29:36.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In that region
at that time, of course.

00:29:36.780 --> 00:29:38.910 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So
everything has to be--

00:29:38.910 --> 00:29:44.430 align:middle line:84%
it's hard to say destroy when
we talk about these things,

00:29:44.430 --> 00:29:47.800 align:middle line:90%
but it needs to be transformed.

00:29:47.800 --> 00:29:49.930 align:middle line:84%
So change the form
into another thing.

00:29:49.930 --> 00:29:53.760 align:middle line:84%
And every time that
we change something

00:29:53.760 --> 00:29:56.490 align:middle line:84%
and we are used to that
previous something,

00:29:56.490 --> 00:30:00.540 align:middle line:84%
we suffer because we don't
like that change because that's

00:30:00.540 --> 00:30:01.800 align:middle line:90%
all what we knew.

00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:04.450 align:middle line:90%
The cells were used to that.

00:30:04.450 --> 00:30:07.170 align:middle line:84%
So that's why everything
is like a kind of a crisis

00:30:07.170 --> 00:30:08.850 align:middle line:90%
when we transform.

00:30:08.850 --> 00:30:11.010 align:middle line:84%
But when you see
the whole history,

00:30:11.010 --> 00:30:13.980 align:middle line:84%
it was because of
those changes that we

00:30:13.980 --> 00:30:17.130 align:middle line:90%
were able to be who we are now.

00:30:17.130 --> 00:30:20.730 align:middle line:84%
It was because of the
explosion in Sumatra

00:30:20.730 --> 00:30:24.990 align:middle line:84%
72,000 years ago that we
basically became humans

00:30:24.990 --> 00:30:26.320 align:middle line:90%
as we know today.

00:30:26.320 --> 00:30:28.650 align:middle line:84%
It was because of the
glaciation in Europe

00:30:28.650 --> 00:30:33.330 align:middle line:84%
that humans spread along
Asia and North America.

00:30:33.330 --> 00:30:36.930 align:middle line:84%
It was because of the drought
in Africa created in the Sahara

00:30:36.930 --> 00:30:41.720 align:middle line:84%
that people left the
rainforest and left

00:30:41.720 --> 00:30:44.750 align:middle line:90%
to the rest of the world.

00:30:44.750 --> 00:30:48.380 align:middle line:84%
The wars in Middle East, not
this one, but the first ones

00:30:48.380 --> 00:30:52.220 align:middle line:84%
were the ones taking people
to advances in technology,

00:30:52.220 --> 00:30:56.270 align:middle line:90%
in religion, in everything new.

00:30:56.270 --> 00:31:00.050 align:middle line:84%
The conflicts in the
Mediterranean Sea

00:31:00.050 --> 00:31:03.320 align:middle line:90%
created the Greek philosophy.

00:31:03.320 --> 00:31:09.770 align:middle line:84%
So everything that today we
see as, oh, that was horrible,

00:31:09.770 --> 00:31:12.440 align:middle line:84%
was what helped us to
be what we are now.

00:31:12.440 --> 00:31:16.100 align:middle line:84%
And people is complaining
about this time,

00:31:16.100 --> 00:31:19.070 align:middle line:84%
but actually this time
is the best time we had--

00:31:19.070 --> 00:31:20.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's true.

00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:21.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: In the
whole history of humanity.

00:31:21.710 --> 00:31:22.877 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's what I say.

00:31:22.877 --> 00:31:25.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, 100 years ago,
we would literally

00:31:25.340 --> 00:31:28.010 align:middle line:84%
watch somebody being
hung on a Saturday

00:31:28.010 --> 00:31:29.223 align:middle line:90%
afternoon for entertainment.

00:31:29.223 --> 00:31:30.140 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Exactly.

00:31:30.140 --> 00:31:32.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And think
it was interesting.

00:31:32.150 --> 00:31:34.550 align:middle line:84%
I mean, actually entertainment
watching a person suffer.

00:31:34.550 --> 00:31:36.380 align:middle line:90%
That was very, very recently.

00:31:36.380 --> 00:31:38.223 align:middle line:84%
In some parts of the
world, it still exists.

00:31:38.223 --> 00:31:39.140 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Exactly.

00:31:39.140 --> 00:31:40.473 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, I agree with you.

00:31:40.473 --> 00:31:44.547 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So women couldn't
vote like, what, 50 years ago?

00:31:44.547 --> 00:31:45.505 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: 50 years ago.

00:31:45.505 --> 00:31:47.810 align:middle line:84%
It's like this half of
the world's population

00:31:47.810 --> 00:31:48.650 align:middle line:90%
didn't count.

00:31:48.650 --> 00:31:51.360 align:middle line:84%
Our minds, our thoughts,
our desires didn't matter.

00:31:51.360 --> 00:31:56.360 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So it's like we
are evolving so fast that we

00:31:56.360 --> 00:32:00.510 align:middle line:84%
cannot be aware of
how good we are.

00:32:00.510 --> 00:32:01.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:32:01.310 --> 00:32:04.460 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: We cannot enjoy
the really good things that we

00:32:04.460 --> 00:32:07.715 align:middle line:84%
have accomplished because we are
thinking about the whole cares

00:32:07.715 --> 00:32:08.840 align:middle line:90%
that is in the world today.

00:32:08.840 --> 00:32:13.430 align:middle line:84%
And the only reason why we are
now understanding the conflicts

00:32:13.430 --> 00:32:15.710 align:middle line:90%
is because we have the internet.

00:32:15.710 --> 00:32:16.520 align:middle line:90%
Because--

00:32:16.520 --> 00:32:16.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We're connected.

00:32:16.880 --> 00:32:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: It always
happened, these kind of things.

00:32:18.470 --> 00:32:18.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:32:18.740 --> 00:32:20.100 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: But we
were disconnected.

00:32:20.100 --> 00:32:22.517 align:middle line:84%
Now we are connected, we can
know everything that happens.

00:32:22.517 --> 00:32:24.500 align:middle line:84%
So that's why we say,
oh, this is a crazy time.

00:32:24.500 --> 00:32:25.763 align:middle line:90%
No--

00:32:25.763 --> 00:32:26.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's over mostly--

00:32:26.930 --> 00:32:28.722 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: 2,000
years ago was a crazy--

00:32:28.722 --> 00:32:29.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Crazy time.

00:32:29.780 --> 00:32:31.910 align:middle line:84%
It's true, and mostly
it's just overwhelm

00:32:31.910 --> 00:32:34.880 align:middle line:84%
of being essentially
shocked by so much all

00:32:34.880 --> 00:32:36.560 align:middle line:84%
at once, all the
time, every day,

00:32:36.560 --> 00:32:38.720 align:middle line:84%
and it's our own doing
in our own choice

00:32:38.720 --> 00:32:40.240 align:middle line:84%
that we're allowing
that to happen.

00:32:40.240 --> 00:32:42.330 align:middle line:84%
You brought up
democracy a bit ago,

00:32:42.330 --> 00:32:44.870 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to talk
to you about what

00:32:44.870 --> 00:32:47.090 align:middle line:90%
you see is what comes next.

00:32:47.090 --> 00:32:49.730 align:middle line:84%
Democracy in the truest
sense of the word

00:32:49.730 --> 00:32:52.050 align:middle line:90%
is every vote, every person.

00:32:52.050 --> 00:32:53.990 align:middle line:84%
Every person matters
on this planet.

00:32:53.990 --> 00:32:55.980 align:middle line:84%
That's the truest
sense of democracy.

00:32:55.980 --> 00:32:56.780 align:middle line:90%
It's not even--

00:32:56.780 --> 00:32:57.860 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: The power
of the population.

00:32:57.860 --> 00:32:58.818 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's right.

00:32:58.818 --> 00:33:00.240 align:middle line:90%
It's not a political thing.

00:33:00.240 --> 00:33:03.890 align:middle line:84%
So looking at it in the
way that everyone matters,

00:33:03.890 --> 00:33:07.460 align:middle line:84%
where do you see the
planet kind of going?

00:33:07.460 --> 00:33:09.980 align:middle line:84%
Everybody talks
about the years 2027

00:33:09.980 --> 00:33:12.590 align:middle line:84%
and these years coming up where
changes are going to happen.

00:33:12.590 --> 00:33:16.640 align:middle line:84%
What do you see as
that next way of--

00:33:16.640 --> 00:33:18.890 align:middle line:84%
I won't even say
politics, but let's use

00:33:18.890 --> 00:33:20.210 align:middle line:90%
that as a substitute word.

00:33:20.210 --> 00:33:23.156 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Well, I
would say government.

00:33:23.156 --> 00:33:27.650 align:middle line:84%
Government means
to sail in Greek,

00:33:27.650 --> 00:33:30.230 align:middle line:84%
because the first
governments in the world

00:33:30.230 --> 00:33:35.870 align:middle line:84%
were basically the king or the
representative going on a boat

00:33:35.870 --> 00:33:38.180 align:middle line:90%
to talk to another island.

00:33:38.180 --> 00:33:42.410 align:middle line:84%
So that idea was like, we
are governing an island.

00:33:42.410 --> 00:33:43.310 align:middle line:90%
We're governing.

00:33:43.310 --> 00:33:45.740 align:middle line:84%
So they were sailing from
one island to another

00:33:45.740 --> 00:33:48.660 align:middle line:90%
and talking to the leaders.

00:33:48.660 --> 00:33:53.190 align:middle line:84%
So politics is basically
the organizational structure

00:33:53.190 --> 00:33:56.530 align:middle line:84%
of a city, a Polis,
which is a small place.

00:33:56.530 --> 00:33:59.380 align:middle line:84%
So we are now a network,
so politics doesn't work--

00:33:59.380 --> 00:34:00.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:34:00.180 --> 00:34:03.990 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Because we
tried to put our politics

00:34:03.990 --> 00:34:06.420 align:middle line:84%
with our morality,
which means the way

00:34:06.420 --> 00:34:10.409 align:middle line:84%
we see things in one place
into a different place.

00:34:10.409 --> 00:34:16.110 align:middle line:84%
Like for example, we cannot
say how the Americans telling

00:34:16.110 --> 00:34:17.530 align:middle line:90%
the Arabian people how to live.

00:34:17.530 --> 00:34:18.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:34:18.330 --> 00:34:19.425 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: It's like--

00:34:19.425 --> 00:34:20.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It doesn't work.

00:34:20.340 --> 00:34:21.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: No,
it doesn't work.

00:34:21.120 --> 00:34:21.719 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's been proven.

00:34:21.719 --> 00:34:22.770 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't work.

00:34:22.770 --> 00:34:23.159 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yes.

00:34:23.159 --> 00:34:25.469 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The British trying to
tell the Indians how to live.

00:34:25.469 --> 00:34:26.280 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, exactly.

00:34:26.280 --> 00:34:27.280 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it doesn't work.

00:34:27.280 --> 00:34:32.550 align:middle line:84%
So each one of us has a unique
way of understanding reality,

00:34:32.550 --> 00:34:33.969 align:middle line:90%
of understanding the world.

00:34:33.969 --> 00:34:36.239 align:middle line:84%
So that's different
politics and that's good.

00:34:36.239 --> 00:34:37.583 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:34:37.583 --> 00:34:39.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What do you see
governmentally as in terms

00:34:39.750 --> 00:34:43.409 align:middle line:84%
of bodies that have to
have some sort of say

00:34:43.409 --> 00:34:44.670 align:middle line:90%
on behalf of the people?

00:34:44.670 --> 00:34:46.560 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO:
Governmentally, the problem

00:34:46.560 --> 00:34:51.100 align:middle line:84%
is that even if we have
kind of a democracy,

00:34:51.100 --> 00:34:52.980 align:middle line:90%
which is not really democracy.

00:34:52.980 --> 00:34:56.047 align:middle line:90%
I call it a fake feudalism.

00:34:56.047 --> 00:34:57.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, no,
I agree with that.

00:34:57.630 --> 00:34:59.310 align:middle line:84%
The way it's been
structured, yes.

00:34:59.310 --> 00:35:03.060 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: It was
structured just because people

00:35:03.060 --> 00:35:05.280 align:middle line:84%
wanted to be part of
everything, so they

00:35:05.280 --> 00:35:06.460 align:middle line:90%
made it part of everything.

00:35:06.460 --> 00:35:09.680 align:middle line:84%
But they made it part of
feudalism, not democracy

00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:10.480 align:middle line:90%
really--

00:35:10.480 --> 00:35:11.313 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very true.

00:35:11.313 --> 00:35:15.730 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: As it was designed
in Greek times 3,000 years ago.

00:35:15.730 --> 00:35:18.930 align:middle line:84%
So we kind of think
that we have democracy.

00:35:18.930 --> 00:35:22.830 align:middle line:84%
But these times are trying to
show us something different.

00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:27.360 align:middle line:84%
Governments are a person that
sails to another government--

00:35:27.360 --> 00:35:30.900 align:middle line:84%
to another place, sorry,
another politics to talk

00:35:30.900 --> 00:35:34.190 align:middle line:90%
in regard of these people.

00:35:34.190 --> 00:35:37.930 align:middle line:84%
So these people choose
this person to go and talk.

00:35:37.930 --> 00:35:42.393 align:middle line:84%
Basically that's a politics of
democracy and a government--

00:35:42.393 --> 00:35:43.435 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Representation.

00:35:43.435 --> 00:35:44.977 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah,
a representation.

00:35:44.977 --> 00:35:47.380 align:middle line:84%
And that worked for
thousands of years

00:35:47.380 --> 00:35:50.660 align:middle line:90%
because there was no phones.

00:35:50.660 --> 00:35:52.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:35:52.050 --> 00:35:55.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Basically
we haven't had internet.

00:35:55.240 --> 00:35:59.080 align:middle line:84%
Today, everyone has a
voice from the-- sorry,

00:35:59.080 --> 00:36:02.650 align:middle line:84%
but from the most stupid person
to the most clever person,

00:36:02.650 --> 00:36:04.768 align:middle line:90%
we all have a voice.

00:36:04.768 --> 00:36:06.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Even if
you're just filming

00:36:06.310 --> 00:36:07.870 align:middle line:90%
yourself popping bubblegum.

00:36:07.870 --> 00:36:08.320 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Exactly.

00:36:08.320 --> 00:36:08.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You have a voice.

00:36:08.830 --> 00:36:09.460 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: You have a voice.

00:36:09.460 --> 00:36:11.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you could have
a million a lot of people

00:36:11.110 --> 00:36:13.313 align:middle line:84%
if you blow a big enough,
beautiful enough bubble.

00:36:13.313 --> 00:36:14.230 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Exactly.

00:36:14.230 --> 00:36:20.680 align:middle line:84%
So talking about representative
today, it's very old.

00:36:20.680 --> 00:36:22.420 align:middle line:84%
Because today, the
people that has

00:36:22.420 --> 00:36:25.540 align:middle line:84%
the solutions for the
population are not

00:36:25.540 --> 00:36:28.660 align:middle line:84%
politics, are people
that have solutions.

00:36:28.660 --> 00:36:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And people that
have solutions can

00:36:30.550 --> 00:36:32.320 align:middle line:84%
talk to other people
that has the problem

00:36:32.320 --> 00:36:34.240 align:middle line:90%
and eventually solve them.

00:36:34.240 --> 00:36:36.530 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
where they live.

00:36:36.530 --> 00:36:40.870 align:middle line:84%
Which before, it was very
different, very complicated.

00:36:40.870 --> 00:36:44.230 align:middle line:84%
So I'm thinking
that the next step

00:36:44.230 --> 00:36:48.430 align:middle line:84%
is to create another system
that the Greeks have never

00:36:48.430 --> 00:36:52.880 align:middle line:84%
talked about because
they had an internet.

00:36:52.880 --> 00:36:54.670 align:middle line:84%
So all the different
types of government

00:36:54.670 --> 00:36:57.580 align:middle line:84%
have been designed in a
world that wasn't connected.

00:36:57.580 --> 00:36:58.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:36:58.570 --> 00:37:01.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And today we
have the tools to be connected,

00:37:01.390 --> 00:37:05.410 align:middle line:84%
to have a voice, and to be able
to create projects and solve

00:37:05.410 --> 00:37:08.830 align:middle line:84%
problems to people without
anyone representing them.

00:37:08.830 --> 00:37:11.770 align:middle line:90%


00:37:11.770 --> 00:37:13.630 align:middle line:84%
But in order to
get there, we need

00:37:13.630 --> 00:37:18.160 align:middle line:84%
to leave a huge crisis, which
is the crisis of the shepherd,

00:37:18.160 --> 00:37:20.930 align:middle line:90%
the crisis of being a sheep.

00:37:20.930 --> 00:37:21.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:37:21.730 --> 00:37:22.540 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Basically--

00:37:22.540 --> 00:37:23.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Behind--

00:37:23.170 --> 00:37:23.890 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, and--

00:37:23.890 --> 00:37:24.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:37:24.690 --> 00:37:30.010 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And I always love
to tell this to the people.

00:37:30.010 --> 00:37:32.650 align:middle line:84%
The only reason
why shepherds exist

00:37:32.650 --> 00:37:36.205 align:middle line:84%
is because the sheeps
believe they are sheeps,

00:37:36.205 --> 00:37:37.205 align:middle line:90%
so they need a shepherd.

00:37:37.205 --> 00:37:40.150 align:middle line:90%


00:37:40.150 --> 00:37:44.170 align:middle line:84%
So it's because
of the people not

00:37:44.170 --> 00:37:49.850 align:middle line:84%
dealing with their own conflicts
that we need governments today.

00:37:49.850 --> 00:37:50.650 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:37:50.650 --> 00:37:52.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And not wanting the
responsibility ultimately.

00:37:52.540 --> 00:37:52.840 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Exactly.

00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:54.770 align:middle line:84%
Responsibility is
the first thing.

00:37:54.770 --> 00:37:57.850 align:middle line:84%
So if we don't take our
own responsibilities,

00:37:57.850 --> 00:38:00.490 align:middle line:84%
always will come someone
to take the responsibility,

00:38:00.490 --> 00:38:04.360 align:middle line:84%
so we cannot blame a politician
by taking the responsibility.

00:38:04.360 --> 00:38:08.040 align:middle line:84%
And those people take the power
just because we allow them to.

00:38:08.040 --> 00:38:10.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So they're going to
become less and less relevant.

00:38:10.540 --> 00:38:11.340 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:38:11.340 --> 00:38:13.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:38:13.180 --> 00:38:17.350 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: But I guess one of
the things that we should do is

00:38:17.350 --> 00:38:20.405 align:middle line:84%
not fight against them, but
to build something different--

00:38:20.405 --> 00:38:21.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Underneath.

00:38:21.280 --> 00:38:22.080 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:38:22.080 --> 00:38:23.622 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah,
so put our energy

00:38:23.622 --> 00:38:25.360 align:middle line:84%
in building something
new, and eventually

00:38:25.360 --> 00:38:27.220 align:middle line:90%
invite them to be part of it.

00:38:27.220 --> 00:38:29.860 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise, you
create energy of conflict,

00:38:29.860 --> 00:38:31.355 align:middle line:90%
and you waste all the energy--

00:38:31.355 --> 00:38:32.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:38:32.230 --> 00:38:33.610 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Just
trying to survive again.

00:38:33.610 --> 00:38:35.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Whoever,
whatever is trying

00:38:35.470 --> 00:38:38.240 align:middle line:84%
to run a certain game
here, that's their game.

00:38:38.240 --> 00:38:40.120 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to play
the game anymore.

00:38:40.120 --> 00:38:41.203 align:middle line:90%
That's what you're saying.

00:38:41.203 --> 00:38:43.240 align:middle line:84%
We unplug from the game,
create the solutions,

00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:46.270 align:middle line:84%
connect together, become
a connected species,

00:38:46.270 --> 00:38:48.000 align:middle line:90%
which we are.

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:51.410 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And also it's
important to know this,

00:38:51.410 --> 00:38:54.320 align:middle line:84%
there are countries and
regions in this world

00:38:54.320 --> 00:38:57.020 align:middle line:84%
or people in this world
that still need someone

00:38:57.020 --> 00:38:59.098 align:middle line:90%
to lead them.

00:38:59.098 --> 00:39:00.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And leave it to that.

00:39:00.390 --> 00:39:01.340 align:middle line:90%
That's fine for that region.

00:39:01.340 --> 00:39:03.410 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: They will
eventually get there,

00:39:03.410 --> 00:39:04.370 align:middle line:90%
they will eventually--

00:39:04.370 --> 00:39:05.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:39:05.170 --> 00:39:07.940 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO:
Understand that, but we

00:39:07.940 --> 00:39:11.420 align:middle line:84%
are still thinking as animals,
as mammals needed someone

00:39:11.420 --> 00:39:12.230 align:middle line:90%
to lead.

00:39:12.230 --> 00:39:14.250 align:middle line:90%
And that's not a bad thing.

00:39:14.250 --> 00:39:17.060 align:middle line:84%
It's just that we all feel
that we don't need them,

00:39:17.060 --> 00:39:19.500 align:middle line:84%
but we don't know how
to handle our own lives.

00:39:19.500 --> 00:39:23.690 align:middle line:84%
So that's why I used to call
the new system ontrocracy, which

00:39:23.690 --> 00:39:25.760 align:middle line:90%
is the power of the being.

00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:27.890 align:middle line:84%
In order to get there,
you have to acknowledge

00:39:27.890 --> 00:39:31.160 align:middle line:84%
that you have the power, and
not the power of the government,

00:39:31.160 --> 00:39:32.900 align:middle line:90%
the power of your own life.

00:39:32.900 --> 00:39:35.150 align:middle line:84%
And in order to that, you
have to change many things--

00:39:35.150 --> 00:39:38.310 align:middle line:84%
how you eat, how you live,
how you relate with others.

00:39:38.310 --> 00:39:44.140 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very long process
to get to ontrocracy.

00:39:44.140 --> 00:39:45.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's starting.

00:39:45.140 --> 00:39:45.470 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: It's starting.

00:39:45.470 --> 00:39:47.012 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All the
little young beings

00:39:47.012 --> 00:39:49.140 align:middle line:84%
that are being born have
different preferences,

00:39:49.140 --> 00:39:51.680 align:middle line:84%
different ways of learning
than what happened 20,

00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:53.790 align:middle line:90%
50, 100, 150 years ago.

00:39:53.790 --> 00:39:56.090 align:middle line:84%
It's already starting
with each generation.

00:39:56.090 --> 00:39:58.090 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah,
it's a slow process.

00:39:58.090 --> 00:39:59.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's a slow process.

00:39:59.340 --> 00:40:01.430 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's going to
be a revolution overnight.

00:40:01.430 --> 00:40:02.230 align:middle line:90%
It won't.

00:40:02.230 --> 00:40:04.310 align:middle line:84%
And I also want to bring
up the whole notion,

00:40:04.310 --> 00:40:05.990 align:middle line:84%
so we can talk about
it for a moment.

00:40:05.990 --> 00:40:11.330 align:middle line:84%
And that is the value in
having as Joan Grant called it,

00:40:11.330 --> 00:40:12.140 align:middle line:90%
far memory.

00:40:12.140 --> 00:40:15.410 align:middle line:84%
She had, like you,
splendid, detailed memories

00:40:15.410 --> 00:40:17.510 align:middle line:90%
of so many lifetimes as you do.

00:40:17.510 --> 00:40:19.430 align:middle line:84%
And as you bring
through your part,

00:40:19.430 --> 00:40:22.280 align:middle line:84%
you're bringing through what you
see, what you've experienced.

00:40:22.280 --> 00:40:23.750 align:middle line:84%
Other people are
bringing through

00:40:23.750 --> 00:40:25.550 align:middle line:84%
maybe from the same
period of history

00:40:25.550 --> 00:40:28.310 align:middle line:84%
where they were in the
story and what they see

00:40:28.310 --> 00:40:29.780 align:middle line:90%
and what they experienced.

00:40:29.780 --> 00:40:31.640 align:middle line:84%
And how important
it is for people

00:40:31.640 --> 00:40:35.240 align:middle line:84%
to start either
choosing to or allowing

00:40:35.240 --> 00:40:39.118 align:middle line:84%
themselves to understand they're
capable of it remembering--

00:40:39.118 --> 00:40:40.910 align:middle line:84%
because you and I were
talking off camera--

00:40:40.910 --> 00:40:44.240 align:middle line:84%
it's the tapestry of
everyone's memories together,

00:40:44.240 --> 00:40:46.160 align:middle line:84%
and you need some anchor
people like you that

00:40:46.160 --> 00:40:48.138 align:middle line:84%
have quite a lot of
memory to say, well,

00:40:48.138 --> 00:40:49.430 align:middle line:90%
this was kind of going on then.

00:40:49.430 --> 00:40:51.650 align:middle line:84%
So people can look at it
and say, oh, yeah, OK.

00:40:51.650 --> 00:40:53.010 align:middle line:90%
This is what I saw then too.

00:40:53.010 --> 00:40:53.810 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:40:53.810 --> 00:40:56.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To really start
understanding who we are

00:40:56.060 --> 00:40:57.990 align:middle line:90%
and what we've come from.

00:40:57.990 --> 00:41:01.340 align:middle line:84%
And so it's wonderful that
you've come in this lifetime

00:41:01.340 --> 00:41:04.550 align:middle line:84%
with far memory that encourages
other people to bring

00:41:04.550 --> 00:41:07.560 align:middle line:84%
their pieces and understanding
of those periods of time

00:41:07.560 --> 00:41:08.360 align:middle line:90%
to the table.

00:41:08.360 --> 00:41:09.650 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, there's--

00:41:09.650 --> 00:41:11.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Lots of
voices are needed.

00:41:11.150 --> 00:41:14.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah,
there's no only one truth.

00:41:14.540 --> 00:41:15.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, exactly.

00:41:15.500 --> 00:41:17.990 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: There
is a fact that

00:41:17.990 --> 00:41:21.000 align:middle line:84%
has many ways of
seeing it as a truth.

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:23.480 align:middle line:90%
So many truths, one fact.

00:41:23.480 --> 00:41:29.340 align:middle line:84%
And if you try to
explain the fact,

00:41:29.340 --> 00:41:31.220 align:middle line:84%
it won't be actually
the whole truth.

00:41:31.220 --> 00:41:34.612 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, because you can
say this happened at this time,

00:41:34.612 --> 00:41:36.320 align:middle line:84%
but there are 1,000
ways to interpret it.

00:41:36.320 --> 00:41:36.890 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Exactly.

00:41:36.890 --> 00:41:37.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:41:37.690 --> 00:41:41.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So that's
why I love to say,

00:41:41.120 --> 00:41:43.880 align:middle line:90%
what I say is not the truth.

00:41:43.880 --> 00:41:45.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is a perspective--

00:41:45.690 --> 00:41:47.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO:
Perspective, exactly.

00:41:47.150 --> 00:41:51.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so this is another
one-- encouraging our children,

00:41:51.050 --> 00:41:53.280 align:middle line:84%
listening to our
little children.

00:41:53.280 --> 00:41:54.850 align:middle line:84%
These people have
memories they're

00:41:54.850 --> 00:41:55.850 align:middle line:90%
trying to bring through.

00:41:55.850 --> 00:41:57.800 align:middle line:84%
They just may not
have the exact words

00:41:57.800 --> 00:42:01.850 align:middle line:84%
that you understand and to
start encouraging people--

00:42:01.850 --> 00:42:04.640 align:middle line:84%
grandparents, parents,
friends of little children--

00:42:04.640 --> 00:42:06.650 align:middle line:84%
to start listening
to the things they're

00:42:06.650 --> 00:42:08.730 align:middle line:84%
saying about what
happened to them.

00:42:08.730 --> 00:42:09.530 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:42:09.530 --> 00:42:12.113 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's really important
to give them the confidence so

00:42:12.113 --> 00:42:14.090 align:middle line:84%
by the time they reach
teenagers like you,

00:42:14.090 --> 00:42:16.680 align:middle line:84%
they can really full on
start taking on their memory.

00:42:16.680 --> 00:42:17.480 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:42:17.480 --> 00:42:20.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So any thought
about that, about just

00:42:20.690 --> 00:42:23.254 align:middle line:84%
the importance of all of
us starting to remember?

00:42:23.254 --> 00:42:27.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yes, we are
living memory of this planet.

00:42:27.120 --> 00:42:29.780 align:middle line:84%
We don't remember
just because our cells

00:42:29.780 --> 00:42:30.840 align:middle line:90%
are trying to protect us.

00:42:30.840 --> 00:42:31.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:42:31.640 --> 00:42:34.910 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: So when we
start to open ourselves

00:42:34.910 --> 00:42:37.130 align:middle line:84%
to the memory, we
will eventually

00:42:37.130 --> 00:42:39.990 align:middle line:84%
know that we all have
the ability to remember.

00:42:39.990 --> 00:42:42.950 align:middle line:84%
It's not just a few of
us that can remember.

00:42:42.950 --> 00:42:46.190 align:middle line:84%
One of the reasons I was
able to remember in this life

00:42:46.190 --> 00:42:52.160 align:middle line:84%
is because I never had the
limitations in my environment

00:42:52.160 --> 00:42:54.497 align:middle line:90%
to say, that's wrong or shut up.

00:42:54.497 --> 00:42:55.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And that's huge.

00:42:55.580 --> 00:42:57.200 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, that's huge.

00:42:57.200 --> 00:42:59.820 align:middle line:84%
I was born in an
agnostic family.

00:42:59.820 --> 00:43:02.450 align:middle line:84%
But even though they
didn't believe in anything,

00:43:02.450 --> 00:43:04.880 align:middle line:90%
they were open to creativity.

00:43:04.880 --> 00:43:07.650 align:middle line:90%
So my mother was an artist.

00:43:07.650 --> 00:43:12.260 align:middle line:84%
She was painting, and
she loved to read books.

00:43:12.260 --> 00:43:15.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't, but she
loved to read books.

00:43:15.390 --> 00:43:17.840 align:middle line:84%
And so when I start
to tell the stories,

00:43:17.840 --> 00:43:19.483 align:middle line:90%
she was able to listen to me--

00:43:19.483 --> 00:43:20.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because
she loves story.

00:43:20.900 --> 00:43:22.490 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah,
she loves stories,

00:43:22.490 --> 00:43:24.890 align:middle line:84%
she loved all the things
that I was sharing.

00:43:24.890 --> 00:43:27.225 align:middle line:84%
And she was like, oh,
and what happened?

00:43:27.225 --> 00:43:28.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I
did that with my son.

00:43:28.850 --> 00:43:30.980 align:middle line:84%
It's wonderful to do
that, because there's

00:43:30.980 --> 00:43:32.600 align:middle line:90%
so much in the little child.

00:43:32.600 --> 00:43:34.040 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO:
Yeah, but sometimes

00:43:34.040 --> 00:43:36.470 align:middle line:84%
when we are conditioned
by our society

00:43:36.470 --> 00:43:38.660 align:middle line:84%
or don't talk this
with this person,

00:43:38.660 --> 00:43:46.850 align:middle line:84%
don't do this, or try to put
the memory or the thoughts

00:43:46.850 --> 00:43:51.440 align:middle line:84%
in only one current of thinking,
so you are conditioning

00:43:51.440 --> 00:43:55.100 align:middle line:90%
that person to forget.

00:43:55.100 --> 00:44:00.950 align:middle line:84%
So it's very important to
listen more than questioning.

00:44:00.950 --> 00:44:05.720 align:middle line:84%
Like listen to what they have to
say, not questioning or saying,

00:44:05.720 --> 00:44:07.670 align:middle line:84%
this is not like that
or this is not true.

00:44:07.670 --> 00:44:08.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:44:08.060 --> 00:44:10.460 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Or you are
kidding me and this kind of--

00:44:10.460 --> 00:44:12.543 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Don't try to
condition their experience.

00:44:12.543 --> 00:44:13.880 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah, exactly.

00:44:13.880 --> 00:44:19.760 align:middle line:84%
And basically all the
geniuses, the people

00:44:19.760 --> 00:44:24.890 align:middle line:84%
that changed the
world, they did it

00:44:24.890 --> 00:44:28.130 align:middle line:84%
because they thought like
children, because they

00:44:28.130 --> 00:44:32.632 align:middle line:84%
had no limits in their minds and
they were playing with reality.

00:44:32.632 --> 00:44:34.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In dream
time and this reality,

00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:35.757 align:middle line:84%
and they took them
both seriously.

00:44:35.757 --> 00:44:36.557 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:44:36.557 --> 00:44:37.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:44:37.470 --> 00:44:38.887 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: And
that's something

00:44:38.887 --> 00:44:43.940 align:middle line:84%
that is very important for
us to remember as adults.

00:44:43.940 --> 00:44:49.910 align:middle line:84%
Remember that you are children
still because we are constantly

00:44:49.910 --> 00:44:50.910 align:middle line:90%
learning.

00:44:50.910 --> 00:44:52.940 align:middle line:84%
It's not a moment that
we say, oh we are adults

00:44:52.940 --> 00:44:54.320 align:middle line:90%
and we know everything.

00:44:54.320 --> 00:44:58.820 align:middle line:84%
No, we learn until the day
we die, so we are constantly

00:44:58.820 --> 00:44:59.970 align:middle line:90%
children.

00:44:59.970 --> 00:45:05.840 align:middle line:84%
And if you allow the children
to keep being children

00:45:05.840 --> 00:45:11.460 align:middle line:84%
and playing with the mind and
games and using imagination.

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:16.460 align:middle line:84%
Imagination is something that
it seems like our societies have

00:45:16.460 --> 00:45:19.530 align:middle line:90%
designed only for kids.

00:45:19.530 --> 00:45:21.830 align:middle line:84%
And when you become
a teenager, you

00:45:21.830 --> 00:45:24.183 align:middle line:84%
can't use imagination anymore
because you are getting--

00:45:24.183 --> 00:45:25.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You need
to get down to facts.

00:45:25.850 --> 00:45:26.360 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:45:26.360 --> 00:45:27.943 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: You
have to go to facts,

00:45:27.943 --> 00:45:30.770 align:middle line:84%
and you have to
make good at school.

00:45:30.770 --> 00:45:32.510 align:middle line:84%
And you have to pay
attention to this.

00:45:32.510 --> 00:45:36.740 align:middle line:84%
Don't go to the moon and
blah, blah with ideas.

00:45:36.740 --> 00:45:41.090 align:middle line:84%
So when we are 13,
14 years old, we

00:45:41.090 --> 00:45:44.340 align:middle line:84%
are started to be
killed by society

00:45:44.340 --> 00:45:48.320 align:middle line:84%
by telling us what is true,
what you should not think.

00:45:48.320 --> 00:45:50.780 align:middle line:84%
And when you stop
imagination, you

00:45:50.780 --> 00:45:53.340 align:middle line:84%
stop many minds that
are able to remember--

00:45:53.340 --> 00:45:54.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:45:54.140 --> 00:45:56.307 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: To remember
not only the past but also

00:45:56.307 --> 00:45:57.110 align:middle line:90%
the future.

00:45:57.110 --> 00:45:59.402 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and we can
have a whole other discussion

00:45:59.402 --> 00:46:00.630 align:middle line:90%
about that next time.

00:46:00.630 --> 00:46:01.430 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: Yeah.

00:46:01.430 --> 00:46:03.972 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're out of time,
but I want to ask you one thing.

00:46:03.972 --> 00:46:05.570 align:middle line:84%
You, Matias, the
kid in you, what

00:46:05.570 --> 00:46:08.420 align:middle line:84%
are some of the things
that just ground down

00:46:08.420 --> 00:46:09.825 align:middle line:90%
into the gravity of Earth life?

00:46:09.825 --> 00:46:12.200 align:middle line:84%
What are some of the things
you just love doing or eating

00:46:12.200 --> 00:46:13.000 align:middle line:90%
or whatever?

00:46:13.000 --> 00:46:13.850 align:middle line:90%
You, Matias.

00:46:13.850 --> 00:46:15.090 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: I play a lot.

00:46:15.090 --> 00:46:17.882 align:middle line:90%
I love to still play like a kid.

00:46:17.882 --> 00:46:19.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So what kind
of play do you do?

00:46:19.590 --> 00:46:21.673 align:middle line:84%
>>DE STEFANO: Well, I love
to go play in the rain.

00:46:21.673 --> 00:46:23.240 align:middle line:84%
Like yesterday,
we took bicycles,

00:46:23.240 --> 00:46:27.030 align:middle line:84%
for example, and right in
the rain and going to cinema

00:46:27.030 --> 00:46:31.200 align:middle line:84%
and doing crazy stuff,
going to play games and--

00:46:31.200 --> 00:46:32.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:34.610 align:middle line:90%
>>DE STEFANO: I don't know.

00:46:34.610 --> 00:46:39.410 align:middle line:10%
